      "message": "Your idea does not solve the problem for me because it involves a behavior change.\n\nYes, most of the linked codes are probably not right to do it like that, but that does not mean we can just go ahead and change them easily without reviewing the surrounding code.\n\nWith this change we can easily replace the existing code and achieve better encapsulation of our string member.\n\nIt\u0027s an incremental upgrade for existing code, and there is no claim that it is the right solution long term.\n\nUsers of `object_path` can do whatever they like currently since the string member is public. So fixing that in the fastest way (without behavior change of user code) should be prioritized over ideal usage which is unrealistic given the current state of the codebase and review timelines for any patches that involve behavior changes.\n\nThanks for your feedback, i did add a comment to the header saying that this function should not be used for new code and `parent_path()` is the preferred choice.",
