      "side": 1,
      "message": "There are at least 6 source locations involving `starts_with`\n\nhttps://github.com/search?q\u003dorg%3Aopenbmc+.str.starts_with%28\u0026type\u003dcode\n\nand at least 4 source locations involving `substr`\nhttps://github.com/search?q\u003dorg%3Aopenbmc+.str.substr\u0026type\u003dcode\n\nThen 7 problems involving `find`\nhttps://github.com/search?q\u003dorg%3Aopenbmc+.str.find\u0026type\u003dcode\n\nAnd 2 issues involving `rfind`\nhttps://github.com/search?q\u003dorg%3Aopenbmc+.str.rfind\u0026type\u003dcode\n\nOne of those problems is in fw update code and was introduced by me, fix is already up https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/phosphor-bmc-code-mgmt/+/91192\n\nAlso, people are adding new usages of `object_path::str` member all the time. If you blame this one, that\u0027s an `rfind` which was added just last week.\n\nhttps://github.com/openbmc/phosphor-bmc-code-mgmt/blame/3b9435fc224cc46f2fa1248388d02e26e4d5c85c/common/src/events.cpp#L21\n\nI am not saying someone cannot do an `rfind(\u0027_\u0027)` on an `object_path`, i just want to make this into an actual object path value type instead of just a fancy `std::string` wrapper.\n\nIf we just offer a fancy `std::string` wrapper to people then they might as well use `std::string`.\n\n\nKeep in mind there might be yet more `std::string` APIs in use on our object path, you can look for yourself also.\n\n\n\u003e I didn\u0027t suggest we change code without review or testing.\n\nIt did not need testing when we did the `sdbusplus::message::object_path -\u003e sdbusplus::object_path` migration. Not every change has to be tedious.",
