      "writtenOn": "2026-06-11T16:04:56Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e I\u0027ve been working on fixing the overall issue for years and fixed a lot of the issues already. \n\nAre you sure the issue did not get worse or stay the same over time?\n\nThere is a lot of repos and a lot of people adding new code, so even if you make progress in your corner, the project as a whole may still regress.\n\n\u003e Awesome.  My strong preference is that we just fix the wrong code.  I understand that requires testing, but that\u0027s ok.\n\nWell if you spent years trying to fix it and it did not get fixed, maybe your way of fixing it is not working?\n\nMy proposed solution:\n\n- figure out which std::string APIs are used on object_path (e.g. `starts_with`)\n- provide those APIs on top of `object_path`, even if they are \u0027wrong\u0027. we can just document them as such.\n\n- merge changes to use those directly instead of `object_path::str` member access\n- not do any testing on those changes\n- make `object_path::str` private\n- migrate users to better APIs (may require testing)\n\nThat puts sdbusplus maintainers back in control on how `object_path` can be used instead of exposing the whole `std::string` surface on a mutable member variable.",
